{
  "texts": [
    "These guidelines are also important because of the problems arising with the usage in the scientific sense.",
    "Concretely, data bias remains a significant problem, as LLMs (like ChatGPT) exhibit biases (e.g., gender, disabilities) in text analysis (Lucy and Bamman 2021; Amin and Kabir 2022; Xu et al. 2024).",
    "Also, in certain cases, when asked, ChatGPT produced hypothetical, non-existent articles, or even generated false data about some issues-like top causes of death in Japan, 2019 (Goto and Katanoda 2023).",
    "There are also basic ethical concerns where authors are leaving the text to be written by ChatGPT with very little, if any input of their own.",
    "However, even with the existence of these issues, to date, most scientific research has focused on meta-analysis or the pros/cons of using generative AI in science, often taking the form of debates rather than structured scientific research or the theoretical discussions on the benefits or dangers of this technology to the scientific system."
  ]
}